<h1><span data-visibility="hidden">The heist of the century</span> <!-- @import "/partials/img-editorial-headline-2.svg" --></h1>
</header>

<div id="editorial-article-byline">
<time>November 20 2023</time>
<!-- @import "/partials/_social" -->
</div><!-- editorial-article-byline -->

<div id="article-content">

<p><span data-visibility="hidden">The Antwerp diamond heist was the largest ever diamond heist and one of the largest in history.</span> <!-- @import "/partials/img-editorial-lede-2.svg" --></p>

<p class="alt--dropcap">The Antwerp diamond heist—dubbed the &#8220;heist of the century&#8221;&#8212;was the largest ever diamond heist and one of the largest robberies in history. Thieves stole loose diamonds, gold, silver and other types of jewellery valued at more than &#36;100 million. It took place in Antwerp, Belgium, during the weekend of 15&#8211;16 February 2003. Though arrests were made and time was served, most of the diamonds stolen remain unrecovered.</p>

